---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
import Figure from '../components/Figure.astro';

const metadata = [
  { label: 'Platform', values: ['Web', 'Mobile'] },
  { label: 'Roles', values: ['Product Design', 'UX Research'] }
];

const metrics = [
  { value: '1200+', label: 'Appointments booked in first 3 months' },
  { value: '$140k', label: 'Potential MRR unlocked' },
  { value: '11', label: 'Studios onboarded into Beta in first 3 months' }
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Mariana Tek Appointments"
  description="A new scheduling and booking experience that enables boutique fitness studios to offer appointment-based services alongside classes."
  heroVideo={{ webm: "/videos/mtappointments_tile.webm", mp4: "/videos/mtappointments_tile.mp4" }}
  heroImageAlt="Mariana Tek Appointments Hero"
  metadata={metadata}
  metrics={metrics}
>
  <!-- Text block (below hero) -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>As a Product Designer at Mariana Tek, I led design for the company's first appointments feature, expanding the platform beyond class-based booking. As the sole designer on the initiative, I worked across multiple teams to shape how studios configure, sell, and manage services, and how consumers discover, book, and manage appointments.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Offset right video -->
  <div class="content-block-offset-right">
    <Figure
      videoSrc="/videos/mtappointments_adminmenu.webm"
      alt="Admin menu for managing appointments"
      caption="A separate admin calendar for studios to manage and book appointments."
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
      <p>Mariana Tek had long supported class-based scheduling, but studios also needed a way to offer services like personal training and recovery appointments. Appointments introduced a new operational model to the platform, helping studios manage one-on-one and small-group services within the same ecosystem.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Offset left image -->
  <div class="content-block-offset-left">
    <Figure
      src="/images/mt-appts-mobilecategories.webp"
      alt="Full width image"
      caption="The consumer schedule expanded beyond classes to support new services like personal training, and recovery offerings."
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>Boutique fitness studios do not offer appointments in just one format. The experience was designed to support a wide range of services, from personal training and private pilates to sauna and guided recovery sessions, while keeping setup and booking intuitive across web and mobile.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Full width image -->
  <div class="content-block-full">
    <Figure
      src="/images/mt-appts-consumer-app.webp"
      alt="Mariana Tek Appointments consumer app"
      caption="Service detail pages on the white-label consumer mobile apps."
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text block -->
  <div class="content-block-text">
    <p>The feature had to work across both sides of the business: internal staff managing schedules, availability, and setup, and consumers browsing and booking services. Designing across both touchpoints helped ensure the experience felt connected from studio operations to checkout.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Two-up images at bottom -->
  <div class="content-block-2up">
    <Figure
      src="/images/mt-appts-admin.webp"
      alt="Two-up image left"
      caption="Studios manage appointments through the web admin dashboard and mobile business app."
    />
    <Figure
      src="/images/mt-appts-consumer.webp"
      alt="Two-up image right"
      caption="Consumers book appointments through the studio's website or mobile app."
    />
  </div>
</CaseStudyLayout>
